    <AbstractNarration>Reilinger &lt;br/&gt;0106571 &lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;This project will use INSAR (interferometric synthetic aperture &lt;br/&gt;radar) and GPS (Global Positioning System) measurements to monitor &lt;br/&gt;detailed patterns of deformation in the continental collision zone in &lt;br/&gt;eastern Turkey. The project will take advantage of the synergistic &lt;br/&gt;aspects of these two techniques. In addition to providing &lt;br/&gt;quantitative constraints on the kinematics and dynamics of the early &lt;br/&gt;stages of continental collision, the investigators anticipate that this research &lt;br/&gt;will result in new and improved tools for combining INSAR and GPS for &lt;br/&gt;monitoring secular deformation of the Earth's surface.</AbstractNarration>
